Americans have started receiving stimulus check payments from the government, and new data shows how theyâ€™re spending it.
Checks for millions of Americans, a central part of the $2.2 trillion stimulus bill, began cropping up in bank accounts last week.
People who received stimulus checks starting Friday already spent 16% on food orders, 14% on money transfers to friends and relatives, and 10% on gas.
Grocery stores are eating up 9% of stimulus checks while 4% of the money is covering bills, Current found.
The fintech startup Current already credited 16,595 accounts with stimulus payments.